12/08/2005
MITROVICA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- OSCE Secretary General Ambassador Marc Perrin de Brichambaut said Thursday (11 August) that the OSCE has to establish and maintain contact with all communities in order to contribute to the processes that are expected to take place in Kosovo during the next couple of months.
De Brichambaut, who is visiting Pristina, met with Kosovo Serb representatives and toured Serb-populated areas to get acquainted with the current situation.
He said the principles of the UN have to be honoured, and that talks between Belgrade and Pristina must be supported.
De Brichambaut will meet with Kosovo Albanian representatives and members of the international community in Kosovo on Friday.
(Tanjug, RTS - 11/08/05)
